# Resume Profiler & Apply — Codebase Analysis

## 1. What This System Does

**Resume Profiler & Apply** is an end-to-end, fully-autonomous job application automation platform. A user uploads their resume (PDF, DOCX, TXT) through a web UI; the system then:

1. Parses and indexes the resume using an LLM.
2. Searches 9+ major ATS job boards (Greenhouse, Lever, SmartRecruiters, Workday, BambooHR, etc.) for relevant US remote/contract roles.
3. Opens each job application URL in a real Chrome browser, fills all form fields with profile data, handles screening questions via AI, and submits the application — all without human intervention.
4. Streams real-time progress updates back to the frontend via Server-Sent Events (SSE).

---

## 2. The Main Problem It Solves

Applying to dozens of jobs across different Applicant Tracking Systems (ATSs) is extremely repetitive and time-consuming. Each ATS has a different form structure. This system **eliminates manual data entry entirely**: resume in → applications submitted. It abstracts away the differences between ATSs through dedicated handlers and an AI agent fallback for unsupported platforms.

---

## 3. Overall Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[React Frontend\nVite + TypeScript] -- POST /upload --> B[FastAPI Server\nPython]
    B -- SSE /status/:id --> A
    B -- background thread --> C[Job Search Agent\nLangGraph ReAct + Tavily]
    C -- result.json --> D[TypeScript Router\nnpx tsx router.ts]
    D -- URL matching --> E{ATS Handler}
    E --> F[Greenhouse Handler]
    E --> G[Lever Handler]
    E --> H[SmartRecruiters Handler]
    E --> I[Workday Handler]
    E --> J[Custom / MCP Fallback]
    F & G & H & I --> K[DOM Scanner\nFast path]
    K -- failure/gaps --> L[GPT-4.1 MCP Agent\nopenai/agents + Playwright MCP]
    J --> L
    L -- CDP --> M[Chrome Browser\nDebug Mode :9222]
```

**Two-tier automation**: Fast deterministic DOM handlers for known ATSs; GPT-4.1 agent as universal fallback for gaps and unknown platforms.

---

## 4. Technologies Used & How They Interact

| Layer | Technology | Role |
|---|---|---|
| **Frontend** | React 18 + Vite + TypeScript | Resume upload UI, SSE progress monitor |
| **API Server** | FastAPI + Uvicorn | REST endpoints, SSE streaming, subprocess orchestration |
| **Job Search** | LangGraph `create_react_agent`, LangChain + Tavily | Multi-query ATS job search, LLM dedup/geo-filter |
| **Resume Parsing** | LangChain `PyPDFLoader`, `Docx2txtLoader`, `TextLoader` | Extracts structured profile from any resume format |
| **LLM (Search/Parse)** | GPT-4o, GPT-4o-mini (OpenAI) | Resume parsing, geo-filtering, screening question answers |
| **LLM (Agent)** | GPT-4.1 via `@openai/agents` SDK | Autonomous form filling via Playwright MCP tool calls |
| **Browser Automation** | Playwright (TypeScript) | DOM interaction, file upload, form filling |
| **MCP Bridge** | `@playwright/mcp` via stdio | Exposes Playwright browser tools to the OpenAI agent |
| **Chrome CDP** | Chrome DevTools Protocol `:9222` | Connects automation to user's authenticated Chrome session |
| **Data Format** | Zod (TypeScript) + JSON schemas | Runtime-safe typed data for job/profile/result objects |

---

## 5. Main Components & Responsibilities

### [src/api/job_search_agent.py](file:///Users/consultadd/projects/playwright/backend/src/api/job_search_agent.py)
The **intelligence layer**. Uses a LangGraph ReAct agent running `gpt-4o` with a Tavily web search tool. Runs 6+ parallel search queries derived from the resume, deduplicates by URL, pattern-filters for valid single-posting ATS URLs, then runs a secondary `gpt-4o-mini` LLM pass to remove non-US jobs. Returns a structured `result.json` with profile data + job list.

### [src/api/server.py](file:///Users/consultadd/projects/playwright/backend/src/api/server.py)
A **FastAPI orchestration server**. Accepts resume uploads, assigns `task_id`s, runs the full pipeline in a background thread (Python `threading.Thread`), spawns the TypeScript router as a subprocess with `subprocess.Popen`, and streams all output line-by-line back to the frontend via SSE (`sse-starlette`). Also exposes a `POST /stop/{task_id}` endpoint that kills the entire process group (`os.killpg`) including any spawned Playwright children.

### [src/router.ts](file:///Users/consultadd/projects/playwright/backend/src/router.ts)
The **automation orchestrator**. Reads `result.json`, resolves each job URL to an ATS handler via hostname matching, opens a new browser tab per job, runs the handler, collects `success/failed` results, and prints a summary. Supports `--dry-run`, `--limit`, and `--timeout` CLI flags.

### `src/sites/` — ATS-Specific Handlers
Each handler (Greenhouse, Lever, SmartRecruiters, Workday) implements a three-step pattern:
1. Navigate to the URL and upload the resume file (triggering ATS auto-fill).
2. Fill only empty fields using Playwright's `getByRole` locators and the typed [ProfileData](file:///Users/consultadd/projects/playwright/backend/src/types.ts#27-35).
3. Hand off to the MCP agent for remaining fields, screening questions, and final submission.

### [src/agent/mcpAgent.ts](file:///Users/consultadd/projects/playwright/backend/src/agent/mcpAgent.ts)
The **AI fallback agent**. Creates an `@openai/agents` [Agent](file:///Users/consultadd/projects/playwright/backend/src/agent/mcpAgent.ts#5-210) with `gpt-4.1`, connects to the `@playwright/mcp` stdio server (which talks to Chrome via CDP), and runs a detailed system prompt with a 60-turn budget. Handles comboboxes, dropdowns, validation errors, multi-page forms, and expired listings. Streams tool call names and outputs to the terminal in real time.

### [src/agent/screeningAgent.ts](file:///Users/consultadd/projects/playwright/backend/src/agent/screeningAgent.ts)
A **hybrid DOM + AI screener** for Lever-style applications. Evaluates `document.querySelectorAll('.application-question')` in the page context, classifies inputs (radio, checkbox, textarea, select, text), then asks `gpt-4o-mini` to generate answers JSON, executes actions, and runs the MCP agent as a final cross-check.

### Frontend (`frontend/src/`)
A React + Vite app that provides a drag-and-drop resume upload UI and a real-time log panel consuming the SSE stream, displaying each pipeline step as it arrives.

---

## 6. Scalability, Automation & Performance Aspects

- **Multi-query search**: Generates 6 distinct Tavily queries per resume for maximum ATS coverage, running them sequentially in one LangGraph agent turn.
- **URL deduplication**: Set-based dedup across all Tavily results before any browser work.
- **LLM-based geo-filter**: Secondary GPT call after URL filtering removes non-US jobs, avoiding wasted automation time.
- **Process isolation**: Each automation run is a separate subprocess with `start_new_session=True`, enabling clean `SIGTERM` kill of the entire Playwright process tree.
- **Tab-per-job**: Opens each job application in a new Chrome tab, keeping previous tabs visible for review without blocking.
- **Resume auto-fill exploitation**: Uploads the resume file first on every ATS, waiting for the ATS' own auto-fill to populate fields before the DOM scanner runs, minimizing redundant fills.
- **Tiered fallback**: Fast deterministic → AI agent. The fast path handles structured known forms; the 60-turn AI agent is a catch-all, keeping cost low for well-supported ATSs.
- **SSE streaming**: All pipeline output (job search progress, router logs, Playwright stdout) is streamed line-by-line to the frontend in real time using an async generator — no polling needed.

---

## 7. Interesting Engineering Decisions & Design Patterns

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| **Chrome CDP reuse** (`--remote-debugging-port=9222`) | Automation runs in the user's existing, logged-in Chrome session — no re-authentication needed for LinkedIn, Glassdoor, etc. |
| **Polyglot monorepo** (Python + TypeScript) | Python for LangChain/LangGraph ecosystem; TypeScript for Playwright's first-class API and `@openai/agents` SDK. |
| **MCP as the agent's tool surface** | Instead of writing custom Playwright wrappers, the system delegates all browser interactions to `@playwright/mcp` via stdio, giving the agent a well-defined, versioned tool set. |
| **`parallelToolCalls: false`** | Enforced sequential tool calls in the MCP agent to guarantee correct dropdown selection ordering (type → wait → snapshot → click option). |
| **Hybrid two-tier automation** | DOM scanner (fast/cheap, `gpt-4o-mini`) handles 80% of fields; MCP agent (expensive, `gpt-4.1`) handles edge cases and submission — balancing speed vs. cost. |
| **`fillIfEmpty` guard** | All site handlers check if a field is already filled before typing, respecting ATS auto-fill and avoiding overwriting data. |
| **Structured typing** | `types.ts` defines `ProfileData`, `JobSearchResult`, and `AutomationResult` interfaces shared across all handler files, enabling compile-time safety across the automation layer. |

