**2.**
> **Built** a multi-agent AI job search pipeline with LangGraph ReAct + Tavily, running 6+ parallel ATS-targeted search queries per resume, applying LLM-based deduplication and geo-filtering to surface US remote/contract roles, and delivering structured candidate profiles extracted from PDF/DOCX resumes.

**3.**
> **Architected** a full-stack automation system with a FastAPI backend streaming real-time pipeline logs to a React + Vite frontend via Server-Sent Events (SSE), orchestrating Python job search and TypeScript Playwright automation as isolated subprocesses with graceful process-group termination support.

**4.**
> **Implemented** a tiered browser automation strategy connecting to a live Chrome instance via Chrome DevTools Protocol (CDP), where ATS-specific Playwright handlers handle common fields and a 60-turn GPT-4.1 agent with Playwright MCP serves as a universal fallback for complex dropdowns, multi-page forms, and unsupported ATS platforms.
